"Scores" speculated killed, though no numbers were provided. The eyewitness lamented that many of those killed were trapped in their homes, resulting in their being burnt to death.

The protest was led by notable civil rights campaigner Dino Melaye.

A group of oil workers protest over 21 months of unpaid salaries. Their company is located at Ohaji in Ohaji/Egbema Local Government Area of Imo State. The protesters also visited the Imo State House of Assembly in Owerri.
A group of oil workers protest over 21 months of unpaid salaries at the state house assembly building in Owerri. Protesters held a twin protest in Ohaji, where the company is located.

Over 100 youths working for a Chinese company, Linda Manufacturing Company at Agege protested to Lagos State House of Assembly over the death of their colleague. The protesting workers alleged he was denied medical treatment after he complained of stomach pain.
Unidentified gunmen kidnap the brother of the monarch of the of Kolokuma Kingdom, their demands not known.

Several killed (varying reports), 80 houses razed over the course of the ten days. It is not clear which villages were attacked on which date(s), with the exception of Rim and Shonong which are known to have been attacked on 09/10.
Gunman, suspected to be Fulani, attack the villages of Lwa, Dum, Rachit and Dyang in Riyom. One soldier, 12 civilians reportedly killed.

One is dead and several others injured in a clash between student protesters of a security guards at their university. Suspected Fulani mercenaries invaded Ome community in Obi, shooting sporadically and destroying houses. Despite the destruction of the town, no deaths were reported. It is thought the shooting was to merely frighten the residents into fleeing.

It is not clear if military forces gained control of the village at the end of the fighting, though it was learned that many of the town's churches were destroyed during the time of Boko Haram control.

Youths under the aegis of ACT staged a protest against a registration fee introduced by the National Youth Service Corps (NYSC) for prospective members.
Limousine and taxi cab operators protest at Lagos Airport over their removal from the park allotted to them at the international wing.

Unidentified gunmen shot and killed the Secretary of Bayelsa State Independent Electoral Commission (BYSIEC). It was gathered that his assailants shot him on the head as he alighted from his car near his residence, off Otiotio Road at about 10.pm.

Soldiers Saturday night stormed Durumi settlement area in Abuja where they shot three Gwaza refugees while arresting others. The reason for the raid is not clear.

It is not clear which villages were attacked on which date(s), with the exception of Rim and Shonong which are known to have been attacked on 09/10 - - Shonong is attacked again on 11/10 causing six deaths.

Ahead of the opening of Delta State�s Revenue House in Warri on 14/10, hundreds of indigenes of Okere Urhobo Kingdom, stormed the premises , protesting alleged refusal of the chairman to grant them audience on employment and other community relations matters.

Scores of lecturers from the Adeniran Ogunsanya College of Education (AOCOED), Ijanikin, staged a protest to the State House, Alausa, over what they termed as failure of the Lagos State Government to remit over 17 months deducted funds to their pension accounts and non-payment of retirees' benefits for three years.

Unknown gunmen in Anguwan Mallam area of Obi Local Government in Nasarawa State reportedly killed three persons after ambushing a passenger bus travelling from Alushi. A police officer was also wounded in the attack and is now missing. It is not clear if the officer a target of the attackers, or a bystander. Some locals suspect the perpetrators to be Eggon youths, but this is still left to be determined.

An armed clash between Fulani gunmen and a local vigilante group at Kankara market caused five deaths and scores of injuries. Following the battle, the vigilantes launched a patrol to find any remaining Fulanis in the area.

Unidentified armed youth attack a truck carrying "cattle and humans" near the government house in Lafia. Government forces respond, beginning the 30 minute gun battle. Two killed, five injured, many others fled.

properties.ALLY_ACTOR_1: APGA: All Progressives Grand Alliance Party
properties.NOTES: Over 5,000 members of the All Progressives Grand Alliance (APGA) from 21 Local Government Areas in Anambra State gathered Nnewi, to protest the defection of former State Governor to another political party.
Bring Back Our Girls supports hold a protest in Abuja to mark the 6-month anniversary of the Chibok abduction.

An unnamed private security officer attached to the Jos University Teaching Hospital (JUTH) was shot dead by unknown gunmen. The gunmen stormed the hospital at about 12:30a.m and were about forcing their way into the premises but were stopped by the security men for routine stop and search exercise before being allowed in.
Members of CAN protest against the planned disinvestment of a cement manufacturing facility by the Benue State government, believing the state economy would be harmed.

A group known as the Delta State League of Online Registration Agents, protested their members' withdrawal as online registration agents by the Joint Admissions and Matriculation Board (JAMB), believe the removal "arbitrary." The group protests at the JAMB officer and later at the Delta State house assembly building.

Thousands of Christians, members of various church denominations protest in Ilorin early hours of the morning to protest the taking over of their schools by Kwara state government, demanding that they want their schools back in their control. The school takeover is related to the area's Ebola outbreak.
Ten are injured in a clash between two PDP factions in Lafia. The clash stemmed from a disagreement of who should represent the party in an upcoming election.

Supports of the APC protest the arrest of several fellow APC lawmakers of the Edo State house after it was alleged they had forged signatures of their PDP colleagues. The protesters called the arrests part of a PDP "witch hunt".

The Nigerian Human Rights Community (NHRC) staged a protest against what it called the rising wave of unemployment and hunger in the country. The protest began at the Ikeja Under-bridge at about 10am, and ended at the Lagos State Government House.
Nursing students protest the state of non-accreditation of their school.

Members of the APM protest the second term bid of the lawmaker representing Aba North and South in the House of Representatives, believing the lawmaker had served long enough and did not property represent their constituency properly.
The people of Nchanawa village in Ezzeagu protest the revocation of a portion of their land by the Enugu State Government.

properties.ACTOR1: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Boko Haram attacks Sina over two consecutive days, killing two and burning property. This is believed to be part of a larger attack on the Michika and Madagali area of Adamawa over the weekend, which claimed the lives of five total.

properties.ACTOR1: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Boko Haram launch an attack against Shaffa (some sources report Dzur) in Hawul, kill eight.

properties.ACTOR2: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: At least 25 members of the Boko Haram sect died in a shoot-out with soldiers at Damboa town in Borno State [northeastern Nigeria] on Sunday evening [19 October] as the insurgents attacked the area, breaking a reported ceasefire.

properties.ACTOR1: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Boko Haram attacks Sina over two consecutive days, killing two and burning property. This is believed to be part of a larger attack on the Michika and Madagali area of Adamawa over the weekend, which claimed the lives of five total.

Suspected Fulani-Hausa gunmen killed at least 25 people in an attack on Sondi and Gindin Waya villages in Wukari LGA of Taraba State. The village is majority Christian, and the victims included at least two church leaders. Some reports declare at least 30 dead.

Suspected Fulani-Hausa gunmen killed at least 25 people in an attack on Sondi and Gindin Waya villages in Wukari LGA of Taraba State. The village is majority Christian, and the victims included at least two church leaders. Some reports declare at least 30 dead.
Personnel of the Ministry of Information stage a protest at the entrance to the Radio House over alleged maladministration and embezzlement during the tenure of the Secretary.
Youth suspected to support different local factions withi the APC clash in Ilaro at a political rally. One death reported.
A factional leader of the Fulani community in Bwari Area Council was killed by unidentified armed men after they besieged his home around Barangoni community at the outskirts of Bwari town.

properties.ACTOR2: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Boko Haram attacked a group of military forces travelling along the Maiduguri-Biu highway, not far from Damboa. One soldier reported dead. The attack is believed to be a retaliation for an earlier attack in Damboa.
The women�s wing of All Progressives Congress protest the non-release of the Chibok girls by Boko Haram,
No fewer than 15 people dead in suspected Fulani attack on Kompany village in Lafia East Local Government Area of Nasarawa State. The attack occurred around 2am.

properties.ACTOR1: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Suspected Boko Haram detonates an explosive at a motor park bus station in Azare, killing five persons and injuring several others, may critically. Some reports claim 10-15 deaths.
Sapele branch of Nigeria Bar Association in Delta State stormed major streets in the city, protesting the kidnap of one of their colleagues on 19/10.

Villagers protested an attempt by a land speculator to take their communal land. One is reportedly dead after a police officer fired a weapon in error. Date not known. Source dated 30/10 cites "last week."

properties.ACTOR1: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: About 30 people comprising teenagers, adult males and females were reportedly abducted by suspected Boko Haram gunmen in villages around Mafa. Additionally, 17 were killed in the attack. It is believed the men and boys were abducted in an effort of forced conscription into their fighting forces.
A group of protesting merchants attack a group of tax collectors Onitsha, causing a melee, 50 injured.
Staff of the Adeniran Ogunsanya College of Education (AOCOED), Ijanikin, Lagos protest the non-implementation of their demands by the state government and the college management.

properties.ALLY_ACTOR_1: COEASU: Colleges of Education Academic Staff Union
properties.NOTES: Members of COEASU, Senior Staff Union and Non-academic Staff Union engaged in protest. The workers are protesting non-payment of wages, non-remittance of pensions and cooperative fund, and poor funding of the institution.

properties.ACTOR1: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Gunmen suspected to be Boko Haram members invaded Pelachiroma village in Hawul council, killing four persons, stealing animals and torching several churches and houses.
Protest broke out in some centres especially in Delta South and Central Senatorial Districts over alleged disappearance of result sheets from the election materials. Exact locations not known.
Hundreds of supporters of Ekiti State Governor (PDP) trooped to the streets to protest alleged plan by members of the state House of Assembly to impeach the governor.

properties.ACTOR1: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Boko Haram attacks Ndongo village, near Mafa, killing "many" people. Mafa had recently been the victim of a Boko Haram abduction raid.
Ten are injured and twenty cars destroyed after prominent chief allegedly sent "thugs" to disrupt an election ballot inspection.
Military forces shoot six, kill two when residents not complying with an environmental order refuse arrest.
A lecturer at the Taraba College of Education (COE) Zing, was burnt to death in a mob action after he allegedly hit and killed five primary school pupils with a vehicle he was driving.

A suspected burglar was in the early hours of killed by a mob after he was allegedly caught carting away bottles of wine and alcoholic beverages from the shop he and his accomplices burgled. The victim was still alive when he was taken to hospital.

PDP Eggon youths violently protest their party's nomination for a governorship seat outside the palace of the local Eggon ruler. Many of the youths lit fires and forcibly pushed themselves through the gate of the palace. Anti-riot soldiers dispersed the crowd. The governorship contenders were unhurt, though one was kidnapped by unidentified armed men several hours later.
A PDP candidate for Nasarawa governor is abducted from his home several hours after he and two others were attacked by fellow PDP members who were displeased with his candidacy.

properties.ACTOR1: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Gunmen suspected to be Boko Haram invaded Kukawa town setting ablaze the Kukawa police station, government lodge and other public buildings in the town and over 250 vehicles. A resident of the town said the insurgents stormed the town in several Hilux vehicles and motorcycles and moved straight to the police station and started shooting sporadically targeting residents, using Rocket Propelled Launchers and AK47 rifles. Causalities reported ("many"), numbers not known.
A group of patients who were denied candidacy for treatment at the specialist hospital protest.
Medical students at Kaduna State University protest the non-accreditation of their faculty.

Staffers of Adeniran Ogunsanya College of Education (AOCOED) stormed Lagos State Secretariat and the office of the state Governor to protest against alleged "anomalies" in the institution, which included the non-payment of pensions.

properties.ALLY_ACTOR_1: NURTW: National Union of Road Transport Workers
properties.NOTES: Members of the NURTW protest after a commercial bus driver dies after being assaulted by a mob of LASTMA official while on the job - apparently, their request for an extortion payment had been refused. Several automobile were destroyed during the protest. Police forces dispersed the crowd. No injuries reported.

properties.ALLY_ACTOR_1: LASTMA: Lagos State Traffic Management Authority
properties.ALLY_ACTOR_2: NURTW: National Union of Road Transport Workers
properties.NOTES: A mob of LASTMA beat up and pushed NURTW a conductor to death after he refused an extortion payment. In turn NURTW members riot in anger.
PDP factions clash at the party's secretariat in Jos over the nomination of candidates. No injuries reported.
"Thugs" stormed an APC venue and began assaulting observers and delegates, causing many to flee.

properties.ACTOR2: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Boko Haram launches a large attack over two days on Mubi, eventually killing 200+ and taking over the village on the second day.

At least two people were killed in what indigenes say is a land dispute clash between Iregwe and Rukuba speaking nationals of Bassa Local Government Area of northern Plateau state, exact location not known.
Protesters in Calabar protest a road's dilapidated state.

properties.ACTOR2: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Boko Haram fighters launched a major attack in Adamawa State, capturing the commercial town of Mubi, where they killed many people (later reported as 200 dead over two days) and released inmates from a prison. Many military forces had fled the area prior to the attack, leaving only a few, who were quickly overrun. Causality specifics not known. Boko Haram militants have also hoisted the sect's flag and imposed a curfew in Mubi.

properties.ACTOR1: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: In a coordinated effort to overtake Mubi, Boko Haram also captures Mararaba Hildi and the entirety of Borno State's Uba LGA. No reported violence in the latter two.
Rioting youths besiege a police station to protest the killing of a protester last week in Ndikpa. The protesters demanded compensation for their loss. No reported violence.
Edo State workers under the Coalition of Unions of Edo State Owned Tertiary Institutions took to the streets to protest non- payment of their five months salaries and poor condition of service.

properties.ACTOR1: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Artillery fire reported in Gaya during a Boko Haram sacking of nearby Mubi, which Boko Haram overtook. Causalities/injuries not known.

properties.ACTOR1: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: In a coordinated effort to overtake Mubi, Boko Haram also captures Mararaba Hildi and the entirety of Borno State's Uba LGA. Boko Haram reportedly kill 5 civilians in Uba.
One person is dead and two are in a coma after two factions of the PDP clashed during a disagreement as who were to make list of the delegates.
Students of National Open University demonstrated at one of their study centres over poor internet connectivity.

properties.ALLY_ACTOR_1: NURTW: National Union of Road Transport Workers
properties.ALLY_ACTOR_2: NURTW: National Union of Road Transport Workers
properties.NOTES: Two groups of the NURTW clash in the Ekefa area of Ibadan over fees. No casualties, several injuries. The clash sparked a protest from another group who wanted to be removed from the union.
Following a clash between two groups of NURTW in Ibadan, a group protests, asking demanding to be removed from the union.

properties.ACTOR1: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Boko Haram overruns and captures Vimtim, near Bazza. Causalities not known. Vimtim is the home town of the Chief of Defence Staff, but it is not clear if Boko Haram's effort coincidental.

properties.ACTOR2: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Military forces and the "Civilian JTF" kill 41 members of Boko Haram in a gun battle in Gur. One members of Boko Haram was captured alive. Following the battle soldiers severed the heads of the deceased Boko Haram combatants.

More than 30 people died and many got injured on Friday morning when a bomb went off at a popular motor park in Gombe. Perpetrators not known, though three were captured by police as they attempted to flee.

Boat drivers under the Maritime Workers Union protest in several areas along the coast of Bayelsa State, including Brass town, and along the waterways and coastline of Nembe, Southern Ijaw and Ekeremor local government councils. The group was protesting against increased pirate activity in the region.

Boat drivers under the Maritime Workers Union protest in several areas along the coast of Bayelsa State, including Brass town, and along the waterways and coastline of Nembe, Southern Ijaw and Ekeremor local government councils. The group was protesting against increased pirate activity in the region.

Boat drivers under the Maritime Workers Union protest in several areas along the coast of Bayelsa State, including Brass town, and along the waterways and coastline of Nembe, Southern Ijaw and Ekeremor local government councils. The group was protesting against increased pirate activity in the region.
Unidentified arsonists set the PDP party secretariat alight in Port Harcourt. No injuries reported.

Boat drivers under the Maritime Workers Union protest in several areas along the coast of Bayelsa State, including Brass town, and along the waterways and coastline of Nembe, Southern Ijaw and Ekeremor local government councils. The group was protesting against increased pirate activity in the region.
Fulani raiders kill a man, kidnap two women and three boys in Umuachi-Afor.

properties.ACTOR2: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Boko Haram attacks a prison in Koton Karifi, overpowers security forces and frees 145 inmates. Two deaths reported, both security forces. Several fugitives were recovered by police in the following days.
A group of widows protest the impeachment of a female local council boss.
The Federal Polytechnic , Ado Ekiti, was shut down following a protest staged by students against a hike in tuition fees payable in the institution.

Victims of various bomb attacks around the Federal Capital Territory, Abuja, protested alleged negligence by the Federal Government. They also claim abandonment in various hospitals, as well as failure to offset the bills that had accrued in the course of their treatments.

properties.ALLY_ACTOR_1: NEPWHAN: Network of People Living with HIV/AIDS in Nigeria
properties.NOTES: NEPWHAN barricade the doors of National Agency for Control of AIDS in Abuja over inadequate government funding for their treatments. The group vowed to protest for an extended period.

Hawkers shut down the ever-busy Aba/Port Harcourt Expressway in protest of the death of their colleague who was killed by a motorist. The situation caused severe gridlock in the capital city, as other motorists scampered for safety following a hot chase with stones by the hawkers. No reported injury.
Residents of Tambuwal and Kebbe local government areas protested the withdrawal of the security aides of the Speaker of House of Representatives.

properties.ACTOR1: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: A suspected Boko Haram suicide bomber detonated explosives in the midst of a Shiite religious procession in Potiskum, Yobe, killing himself and 15 others. Some reports claim 32 dead.

properties.ACTOR2: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Boko Haram attacks the headquarters of a French-owned cement company, steals money, trucks and dynamite. The attackers killed five soldiers at a checkpoint, as well as four civilians.

properties.ACTOR2: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Suspected Boko Haram gunmen carrying grenade launchers attacked the security services in Nafada. The attack in Gombe state came just after midday and began with a gunfight at a military checkpoint on the outskirts of Nafada town, causalities not known.

properties.ACTOR2: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Air Forces bomb Fika town, known Boko Haram stronghold. Causalities, damage unknown.
Staff of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs staged a protest over unpaid salaries and allowances in the premises of the ministry in Abuja.
The casual workers at Midland Rolling Mills, an Indian-owned company based in Abeokuta, protested poor work conditions.
Street sweepers protest over the non-payment of salaries.
Hawkers protest after a colleague is killed in a street accident.
Youths stormed the National Assembly and demanded that lawmakers reconvene plenary in the next 10 days or face further, possibly violent, demonstrations.
A university student is hacked to death with an axe by an unknown assailant. The reason for the attack is not known.

properties.ACTOR1: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: A convoy of suspected Boko Haram gunmen carrying grenade launchers attacked a bank, a cement factory and a political party office in Nafada. The gunmen moved into the town, where eleven were killed.

properties.ACTOR2: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Boko Haram clashed with military forces in Malam Fatori (Bisagana), causing 21 civilian bystander deaths. It was later reported Boko Haram had taken over the village.
Members of the PDP protest in Abuja seeking the disqualification of a party candidate whom they believe would bring disrepute to the party.
Cross River chiefs and other members of the Boki local government protest UN visit to demarcate land. Date and specific location not known. Source dated 10/11.
Unidentified attackers, suspected to be from a neighbouring village, attack Afam Uku, kidnap two and destroy buildings. The attack is believed to have been motivated in reprisal for an unknown issue.

Former councillors and political appointees in Cross River State local government system took to the streets of Calabar, the state capital in protest over what they said was the non-payment of their severance allowances.

properties.ACTOR1: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: A bomb concealed in a plastic bag detonated in a bank line causing fourteen death and scores injured. Boko Haram is believed to be responsible.

properties.ACTOR1: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Boko Haram invades Gashaka, demanding to know the whereabouts of three retired generals who hold residence in the town. After not receiving the information they demanded the attackers set fire to a church and shot a civilian.
Kwara State APC members protest at the home of the party leader, alleging alleged marginalisation in the distribution of elective positions.

Suspected Fulani gunmen ambushed and killed 25 persons (one report hold death total at more than 39) returning from a peace summit convened by the traditional ruler of Arikya chiefdom. The gunmen, numbering over 50 were said to have struck around 3pm at Soni Arikya where they barricaded the Nasarawa Eggon/Arikya road, killing most of the people who attended the peace summit as they made their way back to Nasarawa Eggon.
Unidentified gunmen shoot and kill the head driver of the state governor at Tudun Adabu village in Obi LGA.
Residents of Danare, a border town with Cameroon, protest a proposed UN boundary demarcation which would cede parts of the area to Cameroon.
Unidentified gunmen have kidnapped the younger brother to the former Chairman of the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC) and governorship aspirant in Adamawa State.

properties.ACTOR2: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Boko Haram invades Maiha town in the late afternoon, firing on military forces as they fled with the residents. Soon after the takeover Boko Haram raised their flag above the city. No causalities reported.

A group of human rights activists and civil society practitioners known as "The Nucleus Group" flooded Lagos State Governor's Office and Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) in the state to protest failed distribution of permanent voters' cards.

properties.ACTOR1: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: A suspected member of Boko Haram, dressed in a school uniform, detonates a suicide ordinance at a all boys school in Potiskum, killing 47. The figure was raised to 58 in passing days, with 117 injured (AFP).

Aggrieved members of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) in Egor Local Government Council protested the alleged screening of an aspirant of the party for the House of Assembly seat in Egor, who was last week remanded at Oko prison for alleged attempted murder.
Residents of Ifaki protest a prolonged power outage in their area.
A school administrator is attacked and killed by a group of students after disiplinary measures were seen as unjust.

properties.ACTOR2: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Nigerian forces recapture Mubi, causing much of the Boko Haram population to flee. Several Boko Haram deaths claimed by residents, though specific number were not provided.

properties.ACTOR2: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: No fewer than 75 Boko Haram militants were killed and Maiha recaptured by local hunters. Of the dead, 10 may have been civilians Boko Haram executed while fleeing. Maiha had been overrun and captured by Boko Haram just days earlier.

properties.ACTOR2: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Boko Haram overtakes Pella from military forces. The attack is believed part of a coordinated effort which included Gombe and Hong. Causalities not known. Exact date is not known.

Hundreds of aggrieved traders in Awka protested at the state police command headquarters, protesting alleged extortion and intimidation of their members and customers by policemen from the command. No reported incidents.

A group of PDP youths numbering over 400 picketed the state secretariat of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) in Cross River protesting the withholding of the delegates' list that was the outcome of the party's ward congresses.
Members of the PDP and Labour Party attack each other during a local government rerun election after ballot boxes were alleged to have been stolen. Four reported dead, plus other injuries.

properties.ALLY_ACTOR_1: PASAN: Parliamentary Staff Association of Nigeria
properties.NOTES: National Assembly workers under the aegis of Parliamentary Staff Association of Nigeria (PASAN) staged a peaceful protest over unpaid salaries and accumulated allowances due to them at the lobby of NASS.
The University of Lagos (UNILAG) was temporarily disrupted on Wednesday morning as lecturers staged a protest around the campus over what they described as harsh working conditions.

properties.ACTOR1: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: A female Boko Haram suicide bomber killing at least three people at a teachers' college in Kontagora, northwest Nigeria.

properties.ACTOR2: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Boko Haram shoots two and burns a police station in Gombi. The attackers were initially repelled by security forces, but came back soon after to overtake the city. The attackers are believed to be part of the band which was recently ousted from Maiha.

properties.ACTOR2: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Boko Haram members attack Hong, razing a police station and raising their flag about the home of a military general. Causalities not known.
Unidentified gunmen kidnap the son of a former PDP chairman.

properties.ACTOR1: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Boko Haram attacks Chibok during the early evening, shooting sporadically, causing many residents to flee."Many" killed - exact numbers not known. Following day Boko Haram declared control of the city. The attack is believed to be a retaliatory response for a military capture of Mubi.

properties.ACTOR2: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Suspected Boko Haram detonates a suicide blast at a Kano JTF base, killing the bomber and 5 security operatives.

Hundreds of youths protested in the state capital for the removal of Imam of the Jimeta after the Imam criticised the government's attitude toward ongoing Boko Haram insecurity in the area. The Imam's palace was burned down by the protesters.
Protesters "overran" the local Headquarters of the Independent National Electoral Commission over alleged voter disenfranchisement. Traffic was also reported disrupted.

A group of women from Irete community protest insecurity in their area after an increased report of sexual assaults. The group protested along the Owerri/Onitsha express way, causing traffic problems. Police in the area dispersed the protesters.

Over one thousand women from Okirigwe and Amukpe communities in Sapele Local Government Area of Delta State weekend stormed Amupke Flow station of SEPLAT Petroleum Development Company in protest against alleged non-compliance of the company with a non-compliance of a law. The protest occurred "at the weekend" - exact date not known.

Itsekiri youths protest the groundbreaking of a Export Processing Zone (EPZ), giving seven-day ultimatum to President Goodluck Jonathan to reschedule the date of ceremony to comport with local ethnic sensibilities vis a vis those of neighbouring Ijaw.
There was commotion during the afternoon hours in Ibadan, Oyo State, as a large number of youths protested the alleged killing of an unidentified young man in the custody of the police.

properties.ALLY_ACTOR_1: QOAN: Quarry Owners Association of Nigeria
properties.NOTES: Members of the Quarry Owners Association of Nigeria (QOAN) in Ondo State "at the weekend" protested what they described as "unlawful collection of multiple taxes by the government". The group confronted government tax collectors along the Ifon-Benin Expressway near Elegbeka. No violent incident was reported.

Unidentified persons attack a voter registration centre in the Oke-Efon area of Abeokuta. The area was filled with tension, as about ten persons were seriously injured by the group who attacked the venue with guns and other weapons.
Kanberi and Eggon youths clash over communal disagreements in Lafia. Causalities not known.

Suspected Fulani gunmen attack Alakyo (unknown location) and nearby Shabu, Nasarawa State during the early hours of 16/11. Persons displaced by the fresh violence gave two different account of the situation: The first version says gunmen suspected to be Fulanis stormed Alakyo in their numbers, killing many, and razed properties worth millions of naira. The second version said the Fulani gunmen attempted to enter Alakyo, but were repelled by gunmen, suspected to be Eggon. Specific causality number not known.
Members of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) in Ilorin staged a protest over an alleged attempt to manipulate the delegates' list for the forthcoming governorship primaries.
A journalist is abducted in Abia State, location unknown. The man was later released.
Twenty are believed dead while 56 were injured as a suicide bomb blast hit an Azare market during the evening hours. The source does not speculate on the responsible party.
Military forces shot and killed one, injured three others, when they opened fire on a group of protesters who were protesting against military infighting.

An Ijaw leader is kidnapped in Ethiope East LGA while returning from Kokori following a conference. Many in the Ijaw community blame Kokori residents for his disappearance, and threaten to "invade" the town. Despite the circumstantial evidence the perpetrators are not officially known.

Eggon youths engage a group of soldiers who were attempting to disperse a clash between they and Kanberi youths. Seven Eggon deaths reported. At another place in the city the soldiers shot and killed four Eggon youths who were blocking a road.
Kanberi and Eggon youths clash in Lafia for a second day - twelve deaths reported among to two sects, 30 houses destroyed in the Farin Kasa area of the city - many other residents were displaced.

A clash between people from Okrika, in Okrika Local Council and Onne, in Eleme Local Council of Rivers State has left at least two persons dead and several others injured. The clash began after people from Onne and Ogu communities attacked a group of protesters from Okrika, which led to an intense fight.
Okrika people staged a protest over alleged refusal of the Federal Government to recognise them as a host community to the seaport.
Two union groups (MTUN/OWAN) attack a police station after it was alleged one of their members was shot by an officer. No reported injuries.

Unidentified gunmen attacked a popular hotel in Abonnema, Akuku Torlu LGA of Rivers State, killing two persons and injuring three. A witness described the incident as "barbaric and inhumane." It could not be ascertained what led to the shooting, even as no group has claimed responsibility for the attack.

Students of state-run institutions protest along the Benin-Ore expressway at Dawson Road in Benin City over a prolonged government strike. The students, who carried placards with various inscriptions, barricaded the two dual carriage roads with used tyres, benches and plastic chairs, leaving motorists stranded for hours. They also attempted to storm the state Ministry of Education in Iyaro before they were dispersed by security operatives. No reported injury.

Angered at what they considered as the bleak lot of the kidnapped Chibok girls, impunity and discriminatory law enforcement, leaders of the All Progressives Congress (APC) marched on Louis Edet House, headquarters of the Nigeria Police Force in Abuja. No report of police response.

Police fired tear gas at opposition members (APC mainly) of the Nigerian House of Representatives as they tried to enter their legislative chamber, attempting to stop them from convening. Despite the gas, the lawmakers entered the building, calling for the impeachment of President Johathan. No reported injuries.
A mob attacks and sets alight a man they suspected to be a suicide bomber.
"Overzealous" soldiers killed eight civilians in the Shinge area in Lafia, apparently mistaking them for members of the Ombatse militia.

properties.ACTOR2: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Military leaders report they have forcibly regained three areas lost to Boko Haram the previous week: Gombi, Pelia and Hong, killking "many" (10 confirmed in Gombi) members of Boko Haram. Specific date(s) not known.

properties.ACTOR2: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Military leaders report they have forcibly regained three areas lost to Boko Haram the previous week: Gombi, Pelia and Hong, killking "many" members of Boko Haram. Specific date(s) not known.

properties.ACTOR2: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Military leaders report they have forcibly regained three areas lost to Boko Haram the previous week: Gombi, Pelia and Hong, killing "many" members of Boko Haram. Specific date(s) not known.
Members of the APC protest in Abuja, accusing the President Jonathan and the PDP of "playing politics with Boko Haram."
Enrolees of the public work scheme in Kwara State staged a protest over non-payment of their three-month stipends in Ilorin.

properties.ACTOR1: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Boko Haram attacks the village of Azaya Kura in Mafa LGA, killing 45 residents. Additionally, the attackers destroyed houses, stole food and livestock.

Nigerian security forces fired teargas on opposition (APC) lawmakers inside the parliament complex as they attempted to enter for a key vote on emergency rule in the northeast. Members of Tambuwal's All Progressives Congress (APC) party have described the state of emergency first imposed in May last year as a failure because of escalating violence and have argued it should not be renewed. No injuries reported. A similar attempt against APC lawmakers occurred two days prior.

Two persons were feared killed in a clash between supporters of the Chairman of the Community Development Association (CDA) and chairman of youth association in Aruogba community in Oredo Local Council of Edo State over a tussle for the chairmanship position of the community's association. Some houses were also reportedly razed.

Gunmen, suspected to be Fulani mercenaries launched an offensive attack at Digan Dogo in Kadarko community of Keana Local Government Area of Nasarawa State, leaving scores dead and injuring many people. Specific numbers not provided.

properties.ACTOR2: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad

Students of the University of Jos besieged the Bauchi road campus of the institution protesting alleged increment in school fees. They also called on the Vice Chancellor to rescind his decision or resign.

No reported injuries.

A pair of teenaged female suicide bombers detonated at a market in Maiduguri during the mid-morning hours, at least 45 deaths plus injuries. The source does not articulate any suspicions as to the perpetrator, but many suspect Boko Haram.
Suspected cattle rustlers attack Lilo, killing fifty. The attackers were also alleged to have burnt some houses and destroyed other property worth millions of naira.

The fatality count is expected to rise.

About five persons were killed while properties estimated at millions of Naira were razed when Fulani herdsmen allegedly attacked Abugi community in Lokoja Local Government area of Kogi State. The attack is believed to be reprisal for an earlier incident.
Students of the Adeyemi College of Education protest the deaths of two fellow students when they were struck by vehicle. The protesters marched in several areas of the city.

Two factions of PDP supporters clash over two aspirants to the Darazo House of Assembly. Three injuries reported, four arrests.

A clash between supporters of All Progressives Congress, APC, and Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, in Lagos Island, has left two persons dead over two days.

properties.NOTES: Attempts by Boko Haram insurgents to capture Damagun was resisted by security forces, leading to a fierce battle that lasted well over two hours. Witnesses said the insurgents threw many explosive devices into Damagun police station and shot sporadically into a military base. No causalities reported.

properties.ALLY_ACTOR_1: IGGO: Imo Grassroots for Goodluck Jonathan Organisation
properties.NOTES: No fewer than 2000 youths under the auspices of the Imo Grassroots for Goodluck Jonathan Organisation (IGGO) took to the streets of Owerri burning brooms and All Progressives Congress (APC) flags in the state. They also burnt their party's membership (APC) cards and symbols in front of the Government House Owerri, declaring the APC party dead in the state. Additionally, the youths also declared their allegiance to the PDP.

Two female undergraduate students of the Federal University of Technology (FUT) Minna, were nearly lynched to death by irate members of the public when they were suspected and accused of being suicide bombers.

properties.ACTOR2: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Military forces launch an infantry offensive on Boko Haram held Goniri town, which included an air strike. Causalities not known.
Members of an oil union protest in several locations, preventing all workers from entering oil installations in all eight of Bayelsa's LGAs. Locations within each LGA not known.
Members of an oil union protest in several locations, preventing all workers from entering oil installations in all eight of Bayelsa's LGAs. Locations within each LGA not known.

Suspected "cultists" target and shoot a member of the OPC and a bus driver in Benin following a clash over several days between two street gangs. It is not clear if the targeting was expressly political.

properties.ACTOR1: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Suspected members of Boko Haram sect attacked the headquarters of Geidam Local Government Area of Yobe State. It was gathered that the attackers stormed the town around 4.30 p.m. through the eastern part of the town in Hilux vans and motorcycles. At least 20 dead, including a state official and a cleric, plus injures. A Geidam resident also told [the source] that the insurgents freed also 17 prison inmates before torching the prison building located near the emir's place.

properties.ACTOR1: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: A car bomb at a bus station in Gombe city killed at least 20 people and injured 60. Boko Haram are suspected as perpetrators.

properties.ACTOR1: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Suspected Boko Haram attack a market in Bauchi, seven reported dead, 25 injured. Over the next week the death count is raised to 19. 130 shops destroyed.
A suspected suicide bomber of unknown origin rammed an automobile into a military checkpoint in Bajoga. No heavy damage reported.

Oron youths in Akwa Ibom protested over "undue marginalisation" of Oron nation by the current administration. The youths, numbering more than 1,000, conducted a peaceful demonstration march from Oron to Civic Centre, Oron Beach and Oya Oron Junction.
Police disrupt a Bring Back our Girls protest with a barricade in Abuja. The barricade "enraged" the protesters, though there was no report of violent incident.

A soldier was seized and apprehended by a crowd at a mosque who suspected he was a suicide bomber after he refused to reveal the contents of his bag; police intervened to protect him from attempts to beat him.
Police shoot and kill two Fulani brothers who refused to bay a bribe. The police were later arrested.
Two German engineers are killed while travelling in Nigeria. Location and perpetrators not known.

Unidentified gunmen shot and killed 10 civilians in Tataura. A few other victims sustained varying degrees of injury. The source describes the gunmen as "bandits, "though did not articulate anything stolen from the victims.
Gunmen suspected to be Fulani herdsmen were reported to have invaded Tattaura village in Sanga Local Government Area of Kaduna State, killing 10 people about 10p.m. on Saturday, 27/12.

properties.ACTOR1: RTEAN: Road Transport Employers Association of Nigeria
properties.ACTOR2: NURTW: National Union of Road Transport Workers
properties.NOTES: NURTW and RTEAN unions clash at Lipakala junction in Ondo. It is believed NURTW initiated the attack after RTEAN levelled an insult to its leadership. At least two injuries reported. Date unknown - source dated 28/12.
A bomb blast targeting spectators of a football game detonated and kills a sugarcane vendor in in Potiskum. No other reported deaths or injuries.

An explosive buried at the assembly ground of Ari Kime primary in Potiskum, Yobe State killed a wheel barrow pusher. [The source] gathered that the bomb went off around 7:35pm when a water vendor using a wheel barrow tried crossing assembly ground and stepped on the bomb. A resident in the area said that those who planted the bomb may be targeting final year students currently attending special classes for the their Senior School Certificate Examination (SSCE). Perpetrator identity not known.
Unidentified gunmen kill a pharmacist in Enugu. The gunmen are suspected to be hired assassins, though their motive is not known.

Youths and other supporters of an All Progressives Congress (APC) senatorial aspirant from Delta State protested at the party's national secretariat in Abuja over alleged imposition of another candidate as the party's flag bearer for Delta South senatorial district. The Delta Coalition for Change (DCC) were also involved in the protest.
Hundreds of people took to the streets in Saminaka town, headquarters of Lere Local Government Area of Kaduna State over the posting of a Shari'a court judge to the area.

properties.ALLY_ACTOR_1: MOSOP: Movement for the Survival of the Ogoni People
properties.NOTES: Hundreds of protesters from Ogoniland under the aegis of MOSOP shut business activities and vehicular traffic along the Port Harcourt-Aba Road in Port Harcourt to protest against their perceived political and environmental marginalisation by political parties in Rivers State.

properties.ACTOR2: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: A group of three suicide bombers detonate their vehicle at a security checkpoint killing only themselves. Military injuries not known.

properties.ACTOR1: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Suspected Boko Haram attack Kautakari, kills fifteen residents. Witnesses said scores of insurgents armed with rifles and petrol bombs stormed Kautakari around 7am. Kautakari is in the Chibok area.
Soldiers shot and killed a suspected suicide bomber outside a military barracks in Bolari after she refused to be searched. The affiliation of the bomber unknown.

Four are dead following two non-consecutive days of clashes in Mangu LGA (specific locations not known) between Fulanis and a group of unnamed Mwagahvuu speaking people. The clashes occurred on or between December 31 2014 and January 2, 2015. Note: Mangu and Barakin Ladi are adjacent; each event may have been spill over from a connecting area.
Seven are killed when a bomb detonates on a Potiskum bus. Perpetrators not known.

properties.ALLY_ACTOR_1: MOSOP: Movement for the Survival of the Ogoni People
properties.NOTES: Hundreds of youths from the eight local government areas that make up Rivers West senatorial district protested at the PDP headquarters in Port Harcourt in what they described as the sham primary election of the party for the senatorial district. The group, under the aegis of MOSOP, threatened to boycott an upcoming election. MOSOP held a similar protest in Port Harcourt earlier in the week.

properties.ACTOR1: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Suspected Boko Haram gunmen have kidnapped 40 boys and young men in Malari on New Year�s Eve. The kidnapping is believed to be forces conscription into their fighting force.

"Indigenes" (possibly Bassa) attack a Fulani settlement at Ekpan-Abugi location, Kupa district of Lokoja Local Government. Several buildings damages, causalities not known. Exact date of the attack not know. Source claims the attack occurred "recently."

Unidentified gunmen beheaded one person and shot dead another in Kantoma village of Mangu Local Government Area, Plateau state. Residents blame Fulani herdsmen, though authorities have not speculated as to the perpetrator.
A suicide bomb exploded in Maiduwa town, killing six people; the perpetrator was in the car at the time of the attack.
A suicide bomber attacks a military barracks in Gombe killing "several." A similar attempted attack occurred in Bolari the previous evening. Perpetrator not known.
A suicide bomber blew himself up at the gates of a church in Nigeria's northeastern city of Gombe during a New Year service, wounding at least eight people. Perpetrators not known.

At least 10 houses were confirmed burnt and some people injured in Shurun village of Barkin Ladi local government area of Plateau State following a spill over of attacks between indigenes (not identified) and Fulani herders. No deaths reported. It is believed the battle was triggered by the beheading of a man earlier in the week. Note: Mangu and Barakin Ladi are adjacent; each event may have been spill over from a connecting area.

Four are dead following two non-consecutive days of clashes in Mangu LGA (specific locations not known) between Fulanis and a group of unnamed Mwagahvuu speaking people. The clashes occurred on or between December 31 2014 and January 2, 2015. Note: Mangu and Barakin Ladi are adjacent; each event may have been spill over from a connecting area. One source claims ten dead on the second day of fighting. (Nigerian Tribune)

Unidentified persons attacked and killed the district head of Zangang in Attacked chiefdom area of Kaura local government of Kaduna State, Mr Yohanna Daniel Shinkut. Residents in the area link the attack on Funalis, cause unknown.
About 15 people have been reported killed in Ambe-Madaki village in Sanga Local Government Area of Kaduna state in an attack by unknown gunmen. The attack occurred in the early morning hours.

properties.ACTOR2: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Boko Haram launches a major attack on Baga, eventually taking over the town after military forces abandoned a base. Exact causality figures are not known, though most estimates are near 100. [A source] also confirmed the abduction of about 40 young men by [Boko Haram]. The attack caused residents from the surrounding area to flee. Boko Haram attack villagers throughout the week causing mass causalities.

properties.ACTOR2: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Military forces attempt to retake Baga town, which had been captured by Boko Haram the previous day. Clashes reported; state military forces were eventually pushed back. "Significant" Boko Haram deaths reported. Throughout the day Boko Haram continued their assault on civilian in the city.
An explosive placed in a polythene bag detonates in Lugda (Lugga), killing one. The explosion may have been accidental, though this fact remains unclear.

properties.ACTOR1: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: A sustained, several day-long attack (3-4 days) of residents by Boko Haram of the held town of Baga. Early estimates have 2,000 dead throughout the week, though this figure may be a total count in the entire area throughout the week. A witness claimed the majority of the dead were the old, women and children. The town was destroyed following the several attacks through out the week. 3,200 displaced. Conflicting report: Despite the high casualties government officials claim no more that 150 dead.

Gunmen in the early hours of the day attacked residents of Kantoma Village in Mangu Local Government Area of Plateau State, killing two people. Ten houses were also said to have been torched in the attack. The attack may be linked to ongoing ethnic strife elsewhere in the LGA.

properties.ACTOR2: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Troops from the 7 Division of the Nigerian Army, clashed with suspected Boko Haram insurgents at Mainari village, not far from Kawuri in Konduga Local Government Area of Borno State. Military forces were on their way to attempt to recover Baga town. A credible source described the encounter as "a bad outing" stressing that troops had to retreat when it was evident that going further would not yield positive result. Causalities not known.
The Federal Polytechnic, Ado-Ekiti was shut down by protest staged by all workers' union who demanded the removal of the Rector, accusing her of embezzling a sum of money.

properties.ACTOR1: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad

Conflicting report: Despite the high casualties government officials claim no more that 150 dead.
The bureau chief of several national newspapers is assaulted by PDP youths while taking photographs of a rally in support of Governor Oshiomhole (PDP).
Student's parents of the Delta State Ministry of Women Affairs Primary School protest over delays of renovations to the school.

properties.ALLY_ACTOR_1: ASUU: Academic Staff Union of Universities
properties.NOTES: University of Benin students protest the recent demolition of parts of university by the Edo state government.

Suspected PDP members attack the home of an APC gubernatorial candidate (Alhaji Muhammed Inuwa Yahaya) in Gombe, assault his security detail and ransack the house. The group also destroyed the party's bill boards, posters and buildings. No causalities reported.
Victims of 2011 post-election violence protest over non-payment of compensation from the state and federal governments.
Youths "recently" protest against a still in the construction of a hydroelectric dam - exact date not known.
The Federal College of Veterinary and Medical Laboratory Technology ceased operation after students protest an increase of school fees.

properties.ACTOR1: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad

Suspected PDP shoot APC supporters in Bori. Causalities not known, some "laying critical in hospital."

Seven people sustained injuries while 23 houses were burnt during a clash between Dan Zara and Anguwan Rimi communities in Bogoro Local Government Area of the state. Property destroyed, no life lost. The reason for the clash was not articulated.

properties.ACTOR2: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Military forces launch at least one airstrike against Boko Haram positions in or around Baga following attacks on the town. Casualties not known.
Supporters of the All Progressives Congress (APC), including youths and women staged a protest in Makurdi, Benue State over imposition of candidates by the state leadership of the party.

University of Benin students protest the recent demolition of parts of university by the Edo state government for a second day. The group attacked property of the Edo State Government, set a bus alight, and blocked the entire Benin-Lagos Road for over two hours before armed soldiers and Policemen were deployed to disperse them.

Scores of residents in Lagos took to the streets to protest what they described as imposition of Executive Secretaries by certain leaders in the All Progressives Congress (APC). It is not clear if the protesters were APC members themselves.
A man and his daughter are arrested by security forces attempting to smuggle an explosive into the Federal Government Girls College (FGGC), Jalingo.

properties.NOTES: Following the heavy assault and territorial gain of Baga on 03/01, Boko Haram attacks and destroys 16 villages throughout the LGA including, Doron Baga, Zundur, Kwatar Gumin Masara, Gadar Gajere, Tudun, Mile 4, Mile 3, Dunga, Kish Gam and Kukawa.. The source(s) did not include the entire list of villages. It is believed the attacks occurred on 07/01. Casualties not known, though many sources report the fatality number of 2,000 recorded in Baga on 07/01 may be a total count in the are throughout the week.
Unknown assailants kill a farmer in Akure North LGA. Motive of the attack not known; investigators discovered nothing stolen from the victim.

properties.ACTOR1: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Suspected Boko Haram insurgents launched attacks on residents in Katarko village of Gujba Local Government Area of Yobe State killing over 25 people, abducted women, children and burnt several buildings.
Students of the University of Benin (UNIBEN) on Thursday continued their protest against the Edo State government over the demolition of the institution's staff quarters.
PDP youth protest in Abuja in what they described as injustice and lack of fairness in the party. The group represented Yobe State.
Ondo state students hold a protest in Akure over non-payment of their bursary.

properties.ACTOR2: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Boko Haram gunmen fought running battles with Nigerian troops on the streets of the northeastern city of Damaturu on Friday, in an apparent reprisal attack after a recent raid on a militant stronghold. Causalities not known.
Students of the University of Benin (UNIBEN) on Friday continued their protest against the Edo State government over the demolition of the institution's staff quarters.

properties.ACTOR2: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Boko Haram attempts to overrun Uba town, but are encountered with resistance from military forces and other local militia. The attack, which began during the early morning hours, lasted for several hours. Some witness reported seeing dead bodies and burnt cars, unknown number - "dozens" later reported.

properties.ACTOR2: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Military forces launch an offensive on Boko Haram positions in Damaturu. A total of 14 soldiers were killed in action during the attack, while over 30 who were wounded are now receiving medical attention. The attack comes a day after several running battles in the city.
A suicide-car bomber detonates at a police checkpoint in Potiskum. Two dead, plus bomber. Other causalities not known.

properties.ACTOR1: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Twenty have been killed and 18 others injured in a suicide bomb blast in Maiduguri, Borno State. The source indicated the bomber was a 10-year old girl under the direction of Boko Haram.
1000+ Fulani herdsmen attack and burn Miza location, outside Lokoja. Causalities not known.
An unknown group throws dynamite at the APC headquarters in Abam Ama during the overnight hours. Property damage reported, no injuries.

properties.ACTOR1: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Two female suicide bombers (suspected Boko Haram) detonated themselves up at a Yobe market (along Muhammed Idriss Way in Potiskum) after detonating bombs wired to their bodies, killing 39. The girls were said to be between 15 and 17-years-old.

PDP members attack and severely beat (possibly to death) an APC supporter when they discover him removing their political posters from a public area. Soon after members of the APC launch a reprisal attack on the PDP, injuring five.

properties.ACTOR2: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Security sources and youth vigilantes (unknown group) confirmed that "dozens" of Boko Haram insurgents were killed by Nigerian soldiers in Konduga town of Borno State in a fight that started Sunday night and lasted until dawn the following day. Security forces additionally confirmed losses, numbers unknown.

Members of the All Progressives Congress (APC) from Obio/Akpor Local government Area of Rivers State staged a peaceful protest at the state headquarters of Nigeria Police and the Department of State Security (DSS) in Port Harcourt over incessant attacks on members of the party. The group called on police for greater protection.

An attempt by unknown persons to bomb the All Progressives Congress (APC) office in Ohaukwu Local Government Area of Ebonyi State failed as the Improvised Explosive Device allegedly thrown into the premises failed to explode.

PDP members attack and severely beat (possibly to death) an APC supporter when they discover him removing their political posters from a public area. Soon after members of the APC launch a reprisal attack on the PDP, injuring five.

properties.ACTOR1: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Boko Haram attacks Askira, burn down a school and causes residents to flee. Witnesses report casualties, but do not provide numbers.

properties.ACTOR2: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Security sources and youth vigilantes (unknown group) confirmed that "dozens" of Boko Haram insurgents were killed by Nigerian soldiers in Konduga town of Borno State in a fight that started Sunday night and lasted until dawn the following day. Security forces additionally confirmed losses, numbers unknown.

properties.ACTOR1: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: "Insurgents" attack several areas in Zurmi LGA, targeting pro-government militia groups. 100 reported deaths.

properties.ACTOR1: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: "Insurgents" attack several areas in Zurmi LGA, targeting pro-government militia groups. 100 reported deaths.

properties.ACTOR1: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: "Insurgents" attack several areas in Zurmi LGA, targeting pro-government militia groups. 100 reported deaths.
Members of the PDP protest at their party headquarters over perceived marginalization in a recent primary election.

A female suicide bomber detonates in the Kasuwan Mata area of Gombe, killing three and injuring 21. The explosion may have targeted a military office in the area. The source makes no mention of possible perpetrator organizations.

properties.ACTOR2: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Boko Haram launches an attack on Biu, but are repelled by military forces. 78 Boko Haram casualites reported, military casualties not known. Military forces reported the capture of two heavy guns and five perpetrators. Fifteen of the Boko Haram dead are believed to be Chadian.
No fewer than five persons were feared dead and several others injured in a renewed fight between unidentified political "thugs" in Ijora area of Lagos.
Residents under the aegis IPC protest disillusionment toward their traditional ruler, who they accuse of complicity in murder, arson.

APC lawyers march in Lagos in an effort to put Muhammadu Buhari and Prof. Yemi Osinbajo on the party's presidential ticket. Members of the 'Area Boys' street gangs inturrupted the rally, stealing several personal items from the APC supporters.
Police discover and dismantle a bomb targeting the Owerri Capital Development Authority (OCDA) office in Owerri.
PDP and APC members clash in Sokoto, police arrest nine. One reported death.

properties.ALLY_ACTOR_1: NAPPS: National Association of Proprietors of Private Schools
properties.NOTES: Teachers and proprietors of private primary and secondary schools in Cross River State under the aegis of National Association of Proprietors of Private Schools (NAPPS) marched through Calabar to protest what they called the heavy tax imposed on them by the state government.

properties.ALLY_ACTOR_1: CCESSA: Construction and Civil Engineering Senior Staff Association
properties.NOTES: Construction workers under aegis of Construction and Civil Engineering Senior Staff Association (CCESSA) protest a merger of two construction companies.

properties.ACTOR1: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: A month after being liberated by join Chadian and Nigerian forces, authorities discover 400 or more of bodies buried in mass graves, ostensibly at the hand of Boko Haram. Dates of the atrocities are not clear. Source dated 27/04.

Over 20 LP supporters had been injured by suspected PDP members in Ebonyi State over the course of "the last one month." The number is believed to include the attacks on 22/01 in Ohaozara and Abakaliki, though other locations and specific dates are not known.
Unidentified gunmen open fire on a PDP campaign team in Abua, injuries not known. Policemen accompanying the team responded and chased away the gunmen.

A major communal clash over control of land erupted between the people of Ipetumodu and Asipa, two of the six principal towns in Ife North local government area of Osun State. No reported casualites, though several buildings were destroyed in Origbo. Police later made several arrests.
A group of 227 soldiers protested "unlawful dismissal" after refusing to fight against Boko Haram.
A local party office of the APC is destroyed with dynamite during the early hours of the day. It is not believed that anyone was inside or harmed.

properties.ACTOR1: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: A suspected Boko Haram suicide bomber detonates at a evening market in Gombe, killing scores and injuring others.
An angered group near Kano mosque attacked and lynched a person they suspected of being Boko Haram.

Gunmen have attacked a Military Check Point along Bauchi-Jos Federal highway at Takanda-Giwa killing a soldier and a civilian, leaving another civilian injured. Perpatrators remain unidentified. Exact location along the highway not known or reported.
Striking Ogun teachers protest the government over a payment issue.
A pregnant woman and two others were reportedly killed in the early hours of the day when unknown gunmen attacked Igoh village in Donga local government area of Taraba State.

properties.ACTOR1: Boko Haram - Jama�atu Ahli is-Sunnah lid-Dawatai wal-Jihad
properties.NOTES: Gunmen suspected to be members of the Boko Haram sect have overrun Dzagula village near Gombi. Aware of the imminent attack, villagers fled their homes causing no loss of life from the attackers.
Youths severely beat a commercial motorcyclist (popularly called okada) in Gboko over suspected theft of a motorcycle.
An civilian anti-crime group attacks and kills two suspected robbers.
A suicide bomber struck at a motor park in Potiskum, killing at least seven people and injured 45 others. Perpetrators were not speculated upon by the source.
Some retired workers of an defunct electricty company protested over non-payment of their entitlements and allowances.

No fewer than three students of The Federal Polytechnic, Ado-Ekiti were arrested by the police and detained for participating in a protest staged against the dispute between the Rector and the trade unions.

Several APC groups protest against President Jonathan ahead of a visit. During the visit several protesters attacked the President's motorcade - the extent of the damage not known. Reports of PDP property destruction, including several of the President's political billboards. Police later reported 24 arrests.
JOHESU health workers at the Lagos University Teaching Hospital (LUTH), Idi-Araba, protested against delay in the implementation of their agreement with the Federal Government.
Nine dead and eight missing following an attack on Kente village by suspected Fulani heardmen. The perpatrators also attacked nearby Sontyo.
Eleven people were killed as gunmen suspected to be Fulani herdsmen attacked Sontyo village in Wukari local government area of Taraba state. The attack occurred during the early hours of the day.

Supporters of the PDP and APC clash in Kano after it was discovered PDP campaign posters were removed by APC supporters, causing retaliation. One death repored. Further, a car was set ablaze before security agents mobilised to halt further damage.

Health workers at the Federal Medical Centre, FMC, in Bayelsa State, staged a peaceful protest over the alleged continued refusal of the Federal Government to discuss and approve the demands of their union.

properties.ALLY_ACTOR_1: NAPPS: National Association of Proprietors of Private Schools
properties.NOTES: At least 3,000 teachers and proprietors of private primary and secondary schools in Cross River State under the aegis of National Association of Proprietors of Private Schools (NAPPS) marched in Calabar to protest the heavy taxations imposed on them by the state government.
Health workers protest in Ibadan over an apperent labour dispute.
Two warring milita groups hold a peace meeting in Ife-North Local Government Area.

Forty arrested when police disperse a group of youths violently protesting against a planned Presidential visit. One police officer reported severe injuries. Meanwhile, elsewhere in the city, youths suspected to be supporters of the PDP have torched the campaign office of the All Progressives Congress (APC) gubernatorial candidate.

Following the killing a pharmacist over a suspected business deal gone bad, thousands of youths took to the streets in protest of the killing. As at the time policemen arrive the area, some angry youths were said to have molested the them and made attempt to set the police station ablaze.
A group of contractors protest in Abuja over non-payment by of over N30 billion debt owed them by the government.
Health workers protest in Ibadan for a second consecutive day.
Former workers of the I-Cocoa Research Institute of Nigeria (CRIN), Idi-Ayunre, Ibadan hold a peaceful protest to mark a year they were relieved of their duties and to demand their reinstatement.
Youths suspected to be supporters of the PDP have torched the campaign office of the All Progressives Congress (APC) gubernatorial candidate following the removal of several of their posters.

Suspected PDP members attacked several members of the Labour Party in Ikwo and Ohaozara LGAs (exacted locations not reported), including at least one candidate in Ohaozara West. One death reported between the two LGAs, as well as property destroyed.

Fulanis attack Aeuede village of Agatu LGA on 25/01, 17 deaths reported.

A commissioner in the Imo State House of Assembly Commission, Mr. Tony Onyelere is shot dead by suspected assassins at Orji in Owerri North Local Government Area of the state. Motive unknown - nothing is believed to have been stolen from the victim.

properties.NOTES: An estimated 53 dead as military forces repelled a massive attack my Boko Haram over two days outside of Maiduguri. By the end of the second day military forces reported they were in full control of Kondura.

properties.NOTES: Boko Haram continued their assault on Michika for a third day, engaging in battles with military forces. The military reports several dead, including Boko Haram - specific numbers not known.
University students protest a fee increase, block a heavily used road with barricades.
The Nigeria Union of Pensioners, NUP, Nasarawa state chapter on 26/01 staged a peaceful demonstration over the non-payment of their 15-month entitlements.

Fulanis attack six Agatu LGA villages on 26/01. [The Fulani] had attacked Abugbe village, where they killed eight persons; killed two in Okoklo; murdered four in Ogwule; one in Ocholoyan and two others in adjoining villages. Fulani herdsmen had attacked Aeuede village the previous day.

A community leader is shot and beheaded over a land tussle in suburban Benin City. Perpetrators not known. Date of the attack is vague - source dated 27/01.
Fulani gunmen opened fire on a funeral crowd in Yangal, killing seven and injuring 14.
Unidentified armed men stormed the home of Cross River Assembly Speaker Larry Odey, battling his security aids, one of whom was shot. The extent of the security member's injuries are not known.

Hoodlums' suspected to be working for the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) set ablaze two cars belonging to the All Progressives Congress (APC) in Oron. No reported injuries.
A police orderly attached to an APC government official shoots and kills a woman for unknown reason.
Officials of an advertisement agency, and others, protested heavy use of outdoor political signs in Lagos. The protesters believed the overabundance of billboards was harming their industry.

Youths angry at the Nigerian government's failure to fight [Boko Haram] threw stones at President Goodluck Jonathan's electioneering convoy in the eastern town of Jalingo, breaking windshields and windows on several vehicles. It is not clear if anyone was injured. Police used tear gas and whips to disperse the mob.
Fulani gunmen attack Nwonko village in Wukari LGA, killing 30.

Disabled APC supporters protested the removal APC billboards in Calabar ahead of a visit by President Jonathan (PDP).

properties.NOTES: Boko Haram, as well as a Chadian mercenary group, attempts to over take Maiduguri in a early morning four front attack. Despite the enormity of the attack, military forces and the 'Civilian JTF' were able to repel the attackers. At least 500 dead, - most were Boko Haram, plus civilians. Many of the dead were the result of air strikes near Giwa barracks and Zannari. Injuries not known. A large cache of weaponry was recovered by military forces following the attack.

Nine houses belonging to All Progressives Congress (APC) members and a campaign vehicle belonging to the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) was burnt down at Giwa (Giya) village in Birnin-Kudu local government area of Jigawa State when PDP youth on the campaign train of Ali Tukur Gantsa and APC youth clashed in the village. It is not believed any of the buildings were populated. There was also an unconfirmed report that perpetrators also broke into Omoku High Court. Perpetrators unknown described only as "unpatriotic hoodlums."

Lawyers employed by the Federal Ministry of Justice on shut down the ministry to press home their demands for improved welfare.
A group of youths protest at the headquarters of the Independent National Electoral Commission for a postponement of an upcoming election on the basis of a lack of election materials.

Chanting APC members throw stones at the convoy of Governor Mukhtar Yero as it travelled through Birnin-Gwari and Udawa for campaign events. No reported injuries. Upon the governor's return to Kaduna City a group of APC supporters protested his arrival.
